The paper presents a heuristic algorithm for optimizing the minimum sum-of-squares clustering problem, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The algorithm is based on a genetic algorithmic scheme and uses populations of configurations that are optimized independently in parallel and then recombined. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DM (Data Mining), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Among these, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on developing a heuristic algorithm for a machine learning problem.
